Third-party software and services

This project bundles no third-party code — the CLI runs on Node.js built-ins
only. The list below documents tools, services, and conventions the converter
shells out to, scaffolds into the generated project, or references by pattern,
so downstream users can audit their own supply chain.

Runtime (required to run this CLI)
- Node.js (>= 18) — MIT / Node.js project license. https://nodejs.org/
- GNU Wget — GPL-3.0-or-later. Shelled out by the `crawl` command to mirror
  the live Weebly site. https://www.gnu.org/software/wget/
  Wget is invoked as an external process; this project does not link against
  or distribute it. The macOS `postinstall` hook will `brew install wget` if
  available, but otherwise leaves install to the user.

Scaffolded into the generated Firebase project (devDependencies in the
package.json this CLI writes for end users)
- less — Apache-2.0. https://lesscss.org/
- posthtml-cli — MIT. https://github.com/posthtml/posthtml-cli
- posthtml-include — MIT. https://github.com/posthtml/posthtml-include
- rollup — MIT. https://rollupjs.org/
- terser — BSD-2-Clause. https://github.com/terser/terser

Scaffolded GitHub Actions workflow (optional, opt-in deploy template)
- actions/checkout@v4 — MIT. https://github.com/actions/checkout
- actions/setup-node@v4 — MIT. https://github.com/actions/setup-node
- FirebaseExtended/action-hosting-deploy@v0 — Apache-2.0.
  https://github.com/FirebaseExtended/action-hosting-deploy

External services the generated project targets
- Firebase Hosting — Google LLC. Subject to the Firebase Terms of Service.
  https://firebase.google.com/terms
- hCaptcha — Intuition Machines, Inc. The scaffolded contact-form handler
  uses hCaptcha siteverify. Subject to hCaptcha's Terms.
  https://www.hcaptcha.com/terms

Patterns referenced (no code shipped)
- Fancybox (fancyapps) — referenced as the legacy lightbox the Weebly Unite
  theme used; the scaffolded `lightbox.js` replaces it with a dependency-free
  implementation. https://fancyapps.com/
- Hammer.js — MIT. Optional, loaded by the user if present; the scaffolded
  lightbox guards the binding so it works without Hammer.
  https://hammerjs.github.io/

Each item above is governed by its own license terms — this project does not
relicense any of them. When in doubt, consult the upstream project.
